This directory contains configuration files for vim.

SETUP:
Clone the repo.  Rename it to .vim and move it to your home directory.  Symlink the .vimrc and .gvimrc files to your home directory.  Make a 'bundle' subdirectory and git-clone any vim plugins you'd like to use.


Recommended Bundles:

git://github.com/scrooloose/nerdcommenter.git
git://github.com/tpope/vim-surround.git
git://github.com/tpope/vim-cucumber.git
git://github.com/tpope/vim-fugitive.git
git://github.com/tpope/vim-rails.git
git://github.com/vim-scripts/L9.git
git://github.com/vim-scripts/FuzzyFinder.git

USE:
Once you're set up, just run vim.  Pathogen will take care of loading your plugins.
